@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"



@{b}Train Driver 3@{ub}



Modular Train Driver Simulator

Following on from Train Driver 2, this new version
has many new features, to allow loading of any route with
more details.


  New Features:

  * Up to 100% faster frame rate
  * Trains visible on other track
  * Full steam loco controls
  * Electric token block signalling (RETB)
  * Up to 4 locos on a train!

  New data files for:

  * Horizon buildings
  * Overhead wires/telegraph poles
  * Buildings now any position
  * Square and multiple tunnels supported
  * Girder bridges

  * Many other improvements and features

  @{" Full changes since TD2 " LINK "Changes"}

    Requirements:

    @{b}Any Amiga with at least 2 mb (including 1 mb chip mem) and WB2.04+@{ub}

    Recommended:

    Hard Drive
    A1200 or better




There are three ways of using Train Driver 3

 * Generate a random route by adjusting the sliders on the @{" Loading Screen " LINK "Load_Screen"}
   The random routes generated by TD3 will be different from those generated by TD2 with the same code

 * Load data from a real railway route

 * Create a real or fictional route using @{" Data files " LINK "Data"} or
    @{" Train Driver Route Editor " LINK "TDRE"}



On Line Help is always available by pressing the Help key.
You need Amigaguide in your Workbench C: drawer for this to work


